00:13:20.075 --> 00:13:21.283
Okay, kid?
Night.

253
00:13:23.578 --> 00:13:24.953
Dad?
Yo.

254
00:13:26.498 --> 00:13:27.790
Glad you're home.

255
00:13:28.208 --> 00:13:30.084
Thanks. I appreciate it.

256
00:13:30.752 --> 00:13:32.419
And we'll play tomorrow,
okay?

257
00:13:33.171 --> 00:13:34.838
Maybe you can show me
your English teacher.

258
00:13:34.923 --> 00:13:36.215
She's pretty hot, too.

259
00:13:36.299 --> 00:13:37.883
Nah!
Yeah.

260
00:13:37.967 --> 00:13:39.385
Good night, kid.

261
00:13:39.469 --> 00:13:41.303
You deserve the
worst for what you did.

262
00:13:42.472 --> 00:13:44.556
Paulie, it wasn't your
money. It was Rocky's money.

263
00:13:44.641 --> 00:13:46.392
You gonna be hysterical?
You cost us everything.

264
00:13:46.476 --> 00:13:48.394
That's what I need.
It was a mistake.

265
00:13:48.478 --> 00:13:51.230
You think I thought this
all was gonna happen?

266
00:13:51.314 --> 00:13:52.981
Don't you walk
away from me.

267
00:13:53.066 --> 00:13:55.692
You just gave up
our life!

268
00:13:56.152 --> 00:13:58.487
And you think it's
like some stupid thing?

269
00:13:58.571 --> 00:14:01.240
Paulie! Paulie, do you know what you did?

270
00:14:01.324 --> 00:14:02.783
Do you know the seriousness of what you did?

271
00:14:02.867 --> 00:14:03.909
I understand it!

272
00:14:03.993 --> 00:14:05.327
Do you?
Then answer me!

273
00:14:05.412 --> 00:14:07.287
I understand
the whole freaking thing!

274
00:14:07.372 --> 00:14:10.749
I understand it! Your
accountant's the crook, not me!

275
00:14:10.834 --> 00:14:12.543
I did what I
thought was right.

276
00:14:12.627 --> 00:14:14.044
So, now, don't blame me for nothing.

277
00:14:14.129 --> 00:14:16.505
I want to murder the bum
worse than anybody.

278
00:14:16.589 --> 00:14:18.590
Hey, Adrian,
what's wrong?

279
00:14:18.675 --> 00:14:20.259
Look what you done now.

280
00:14:20.343 --> 00:14:21.427
She's dumping
everything on me.

281
00:14:21.511 --> 00:14:23.262
Come on, Paulie.
Don't turn this around on me.

282
00:14:23.346 --> 00:14:24.555
Come on, what'd you do, Paulie?

283
00:14:24.639 --> 00:14:26.098
He gave power...

284
00:14:26.182 --> 00:14:28.142
Power of attorney to our accountant. What?

285
00:14:28.226 --> 00:14:32.062
Gave... I just didn't gave
anything to nobody, huh?

286
00:14:32.147 --> 00:14:33.230
He sent a letter!

287
00:14:33.314 --> 00:14:35.732
He says we're gonna be in Russia
a couple of months. He says,

288
00:14:35.817 --> 00:14:38.277
"And I need Rocky
to sign a tax extension!"

289
00:14:38.361 --> 00:14:42.114
Not an extension! That was
a power of attorney, Paulie!

290
00:14:42.198 --> 00:14:44.700
He's the thief!
I need alcohol.

291
00:14:45.452 --> 00:14:48.203
Rocky, on my eyes, I never
stole a freaking dime.

292
00:14:49.205 --> 00:14:51.373
Adrian,
what's happening here?

293
00:14:51.958 --> 00:14:52.958
It's gone.

294
00:14:53.042 --> 00:14:54.168
What's gone?

295
00:14:54.252 --> 00:14:55.878
The money.
The money.

296
00:14:55.962 --> 00:14:57.838
Everything.
It's all gone.

297
00:14:58.548 --> 00:15:00.132
The piece of paper
Paulie had you sign

298
00:15:00.216 --> 00:15:02.968
wasn't a request for an
extension on your tax returns.

299
00:15:03.052 --> 00:15:07.055
It was a blanket power of attorney
in favor of the accountant,

300
00:15:07.140 --> 00:15:10.142
who was involved in some very
high-priced commercial real estate.

301
00:15:10.226 --> 00:15:12.311
He thought he could flip
it quick, take his profit,

302
00:15:12.395 --> 00:15:14.438
have your money back
before you knew it was gone.

303
00:15:14.522 --> 00:15:17.316
And unfortunately for you
and everybody in this room,

304
00:15:17.400 --> 00:15:20.152
his deals fell through
because the market dried up.

305
00:15:20.236 --> 00:15:21.778
And you lost millions.

306
00:15:21.863 --> 00:15:23.655
So, what are you saying? There
ain't nothing I can do about it?

307
00:15:23.740 --> 00:15:26.241
I'm doing plenty. I've filed
eight criminal acts against him,

308
00:15:26.326 --> 00:15:29.077
but you've got tremendous debt
payment on this property, Rocky.

309
00:15:29.162 --> 00:15:31.330
You didn't pay your tax returns in six years,

310
00:15:31.414 --> 00:15:33.624
and the mortgage on your house
hasn't been paid in months.

311
00:15:33.708 --> 00:15:37.169
Wait, we didn't have a mortgage.
Our house was fully paid for.

312
00:15:37.253 --> 00:15:38.712
Don't take it from me.
Ask him.

313
00:15:38.796 --> 00:15:42.508
Apparently not. There's nearly
$400,000 still outstanding.

314
00:15:42.592 --> 00:15:44.384
The only thing you have
that's not encumbered

315
00:15:44.469 --> 00:15:46.428
is a gymnasium that was
willed to your son

316
00:15:46.513 --> 00:15:49.515
by a Mickey Goldmill
in 1982.

317
00:15:49.599 --> 00:15:52.184
You can sell some things.
Remember those commercials you did?

318
00:15:52.268 --> 00:15:54.645
You know, Paulie, I ain't
no commercial kind of guy.

319
00:15:54.729 --> 00:15:56.563
I'm a fighter.
It's what I do for a living.

320
00:15:56.648 --> 00:15:59.149
Nah, it's just as well.
We couldn't get any sponsors.

321
00:15:59.234 --> 00:16:01.193
With the investigation
of the accountant,

322
00:16:01.277 --> 00:16:03.487
out pops a criminal record
of Rocky's for assault

323
00:16:03.571 --> 00:16:05.113
in connection
with loan sharking.

324
00:16:05.198 --> 00:16:07.491
But that was a long time
ago. He didn't know what...

325
00:16:07.575 --> 00:16:09.076
Why not a couple more fights?

326
00:16:09.160 --> 00:16:10.369
With your
popularity right now,

327
00:16:10.453 --> 00:16:11.912
you could be out of
this thing in no time.

328
00:16:11.996 --> 00:16:13.038
No, he's retiring.

329
00:16:13.122 --> 00:16:14.540
Rocko, fighting's the ticket.

330
00:16:14.624 --> 00:16:16.542
I said he's retired!

331
00:16:16.626 --> 00:16:18.460
Paulie, we're here
because of you!

332
00:16:19.087 --> 00:16:21.338
I'm not taking
the heat for all this.

333
00:16:21.422 --> 00:16:23.048
I thought I was
doing smart business.

334
00:16:23.132 --> 00:16:25.133
You thought you
did smart business?

335
00:16:25.218 --> 00:16:26.176
Hey, you...
Me?

336
00:16:26.302 --> 00:16:28.178
What are you talking about me?
The accountant was your choice!

337
00:16:28.304 --> 00:16:29.596
My choice? You should
have known he was a thief,

338
00:16:29.681 --> 00:16:30.681
but you're never awake

339
00:16:30.765 --> 00:16:33.350
because you live in this fairy-tale
world where the air don't move.

340
00:16:33.476 --> 00:16:35.310
Paulie... You're like a
season that don't change!

341
00:16:35.395 --> 00:16:36.728
Hey, you don't
talk to her like this.

342
00:16:36.813 --> 00:16:38.438
I'm not no tomato
can you kick around!

343
00:16:38.523 --> 00:16:39.856
Paulie, no!
Yeah!

344
00:16:39.983 --> 00:16:42.317
You call Duke. You tell him I'll fight Cane.

345
00:16:42.402 --> 00:16:44.069
I don't care,
anywhere, anytime.

346
00:16:44.195 --> 00:16:45.362
- No, Rocky.
- If that's what you want,

347
00:16:45.446 --> 00:16:46.572
I'll get on it right away.

348
00:16:46.656 --> 00:16:47.739
No. No.

349
00:16:47.824 --> 00:16:48.824
Rocky, Rocky, please.

350
00:16:48.908 --> 00:16:51.702
We can't go down like this. A couple
of fights, we're out of trouble, Adrian.

351
00:16:51.786 --> 00:16:52.911
Yeah, but you said you wouldn't.

352
00:16:52.996 --> 00:16:54.121
No, I didn't say anything.

353
00:16:54.205 --> 00:16:55.455
Look, did we come
this far to lose it?

354
00:16:55.540 --> 00:16:57.124
Well, you know, you have to see a doctor.

355
00:16:57.208 --> 00:16:58.584
Adrian, I don't need to see no doctor.

356
00:16:58.668 --> 00:16:59.710
I need to get
a promoter.

357
00:16:59.794 --> 00:17:00.877
Hey, you know, you gotta see a doctor.

358
00:17:01.004 --> 00:17:02.796
If he says it's all right, I'll
support anything you wanna do.

359
00:17:02.880 --> 00:17:04.047
I gotta fight, okay?

360
00:17:04.132 --> 00:17:05.591
I got problems.
I gotta fight.

361
00:17:06.467 --> 00:17:08.218
Will you do it for me?

362
00:17:10.513 --> 00:17:12.139
All right, for you.

363
00:17:13.099 --> 00:17:16.101
Because of the continuous
violent blows to the head,

364
00:17:16.185 --> 00:17:18.353
you've developed a condition
particular to boxers

365
00:17:18.438 --> 00:17:20.772
called cavum
septum pellucidum,

366
00:17:20.857 --> 00:17:24.276
which is a hole in the membrane
separating the ventricles.

367
00:17:24.360 --> 00:17:28.155
The brain's surface neurons in this
area have also been traumatized.

368
00:17:28.239 --> 00:17:30.741
Excuse me, Doctor.
Simply stated, Mr. Balboa,

369
00:17:30.825 --> 00:17:33.952
it means that you've suffered
some damage to the brain.

370
00:17:34.037 --> 00:17:35.954
How long until he recovers?

371
00:17:36.039 --> 00:17:37.664
The effects
are irreversible.

372
00:17:38.916 --> 00:17:42.628
I... Rocky,
you have to retire.

373
00:17:42.712 --> 00:17:44.046
Adrian,
I don't want to retire.

374
00:17:44.130 --> 00:17:45.756
You know, this ain't
the time to retire.

375
00:17:45.840 --> 00:17:48.425
No, not in here,
not in no office.

376
00:17:49.052 --> 00:17:52.804
I just fought the best fight of
my life. I just did that, you know,

377
00:17:54.265 --> 00:17:56.808
and all I need
is a couple more.

378
00:17:56.893 --> 00:17:59.353
No, Rocky, you suffered severe brain trauma.

379
00:17:59.437 --> 00:18:01.146
Well, he could be wrong.
Anybody could be wrong.

380
00:18:01.230 --> 00:18:02.230
I don't think he is.

381
00:18:02.315 --> 00:18:04.483
He ain't God. Look, Adrian,
only God ain't wrong.

382
00:18:04.567 --> 00:18:06.860
Hey, Rocky,
this is what's good for you.

383
00:18:06.944 --> 00:18:08.654
All I need is
a couple easy ones, right?

384
00:18:08.738 --> 00:18:11.114
Not with the way it is. You
can't get licensed in any state.

385
00:18:11.199 --> 00:18:13.575
He can't get
licensed anyway, Doctor?

386
00:18:13.660 --> 00:18:14.785
That is correct.

387
00:18:15.411 --> 00:18:17.871
Rocky,
do you love me?

388
00:18:20.083 --> 00:18:22.000
Yeah, I love you.
Why you ask that?

389
00:18:22.085 --> 00:18:24.670
Because if you
love somebody,

390
00:18:24.754 --> 00:18:26.838
you live with them,
you live for them.

391
00:18:26.923 --> 00:18:28.965
You don't gamble
with a life.

392
00:18:29.050 --> 00:18:32.010
Rocky, I don't care about the money.
It's you.

393
00:18:33.137 --> 00:18:34.930
That's all that matters.

394
00:18:36.557 --> 00:18:40.602
Please. We'll be okay. We'll be fine.

395
00:18:44.524 --> 00:18:45.774
No one's gotta know...

396
00:18:47.819 --> 00:18:48.944
Uh...

397
00:18:51.197 --> 00:18:53.156
No one has to know,
doctor, right?

398
00:18:53.241 --> 00:18:55.117
It'll be
strictly confidential.

399
00:18:59.872 --> 00:19:01.206
Thank you.

400
00:19:20.810 --> 00:19:23.729
May we hear
our next bid, please?

401
00:19:23.813 --> 00:19:25.063
Are you done?

402
00:19:26.274 --> 00:19:27.399
Sold.

403
00:19:30.653 --> 00:19:33.780
Moving along, ladies and
gentlemen, item number 46.

404
00:19:33.865 --> 00:19:36.158
Hey, kid.
Bike's been sold.

405
00:19:36.993 --> 00:19:39.578
Hey, bike's been sold.
Get off the bike. Come on.

406
00:19:43.666 --> 00:19:47.669
We have an opening bid.
$25,000 is the bid.

407
00:19:49.213 --> 00:19:51.465
Don't worry about it.
We've been down before.

408
00:19:51.799 --> 00:19:53.133
I'll get it all back.

409
00:19:53.217 --> 00:19:55.343
We just gotta stick together,
all right?

410
00:19:55.428 --> 00:19:56.762
Home team.

411
00:19:56.846 --> 00:19:57.846
Yeah, right.

412
00:19:57.930 --> 00:19:59.055
Sold.

413
00:19:59.682 --> 00:20:01.683
Come on, you know,
Mickey used to say

414
00:20:01.768 --> 00:20:04.144
a fight ain't over
till you heard the bell.

415
00:20:04.228 --> 00:20:05.937
We ain't heard
a bell yet, have we?

416
00:20:06.022 --> 00:20:09.983
Rocky Balboa's boxing gloves
from his first heavyweight fight.

417
00:20:27.627 --> 00:20:28.960
Rocky?

418
00:20:30.630 --> 00:20:32.005
Hey, it still fits.

419
00:20:35.051 --> 00:20:37.552
Why you wearing
those clothes?

420
00:20:37.637 --> 00:20:40.639
I was just going through some of
the stuff up there, and I found 'em,

421
00:20:40.723 --> 00:20:43.016
and they feel kind of
comfortable, you know?

422
00:20:43.100 --> 00:20:46.269
Well, I was looking all
over for you downstairs.

423
00:20:46.354 --> 00:20:47.312
It's kind of
depressing.

424
00:20:47.396 --> 00:20:50.106
Yeah, I know
what you mean.

425
00:20:50.191 --> 00:20:53.318
What's this
doing in your ear?

426
00:20:53.402 --> 00:20:54.528
What? Oh, God.

427
00:20:54.612 --> 00:20:56.112
Remember these?

428
00:20:56.823 --> 00:20:58.657
I... Yeah.

429
00:20:58.741 --> 00:21:00.492
Go ahead.
You...

430
00:21:00.701 --> 00:21:01.701
I remember when
you took them off.

431
00:21:01.786 --> 00:21:02.828
That's right.

432
00:21:02.912 --> 00:21:05.747
First time I ever
kissed you, remember?

433
00:21:06.040 --> 00:21:07.249
Kiss me.

434
00:21:09.085 --> 00:21:12.838
Adrian, I want to go out
for a little bit, you know?

435
00:21:12.922 --> 00:21:14.673
Just take a little walk.

436
00:21:14.757 --> 00:21:16.341
I just wanna
feel better, but...

437
00:21:16.425 --> 00:21:19.302
Hey, could you talk to the kid?
'Cause he's...

438
00:21:19.720 --> 00:21:20.720
He's really taking
this hard, you know?

439
00:21:20.805 --> 00:21:21.888
Sure.

440
00:21:22.014 --> 00:21:23.014
Okay?

441
00:21:23.891 --> 00:21:24.933
Where you going?

442
00:21:25.017 --> 00:21:26.810
I thought I'd go to Andy's.

443
00:22:11.772 --> 00:22:13.690
How you doing, Mick?

444
00:23:24.428 --> 00:23:25.804
Slip the jab.

445
00:23:27.765 --> 00:23:29.224
Slip the jab.
Slip the jab.

446
00:23:29.308 --> 00:23:30.725
Slip the jab,
will ya?

447
00:23:32.311 --> 00:23:33.395
Slip the jab!

448
00:23:36.315 --> 00:23:38.441
That's right.
That's it.

449
00:23:38.526 --> 00:23:40.276
Hey, I didn't
hear no bell!

450
00:23:40.361 --> 00:23:41.569
Okay.

451
00:23:42.405 --> 00:23:43.822
All right. That's right.

452
00:23:43.906 --> 00:23:47.492
Slip the jab.
That's it. Mentalize.

453
00:23:47.576 --> 00:23:49.703
See that bum
in front of you.

454
00:23:49.787 --> 00:23:52.914
You see yourself doing right,
and you do right.

455
00:23:54.041 --> 00:23:56.001
That's pretty.
That's very pretty.

456
00:23:56.669 --> 00:23:58.336
Time!

457
00:23:58.421 --> 00:24:01.840
Come here, Rock. My God,
you're ready, ain't you?

458
00:24:01.924 --> 00:24:03.466
And Apollo won't
know what hit him.

459
00:24:03.551 --> 00:24:07.721
You're gonna roll over him like
a bulldozer, an Italian bulldozer.

460
00:24:08.389 --> 00:24:10.181
You know, kid,
I know how you feel

461
00:24:10.266 --> 00:24:12.267
about this fight
that's coming up.

462
00:24:12.685 --> 00:24:15.020
Because
I was young once, too.

463
00:24:16.063 --> 00:24:17.522
And I tell you something.

464
00:24:18.816 --> 00:24:24.320
Well, if you wasn't here, I
probably wouldn't be alive today.

465
00:24:24.864 --> 00:24:26.948
The fact that you're here

466
00:24:27.033 --> 00:24:29.868
and doing as well
as you're doing gives me,

467
00:24:29.952 --> 00:24:33.621
what do you call it, a
motivization to stay alive?

468
00:24:34.248 --> 00:24:36.833
'Cause I think that
people die sometimes

469
00:24:36.917 --> 00:24:38.460
when they don't
wanna live no more.

470
00:24:38.961 --> 00:24:41.129
"Nature's smarter
than people think."

471
00:24:41.213 --> 00:24:43.548
And nature is smarter
than people think.

472
00:24:43.632 --> 00:24:46.801
Little by little, we lose our
friends, we lose everything.

473
00:24:46.886 --> 00:24:49.971
We keep losing and
losing till we say,

474
00:24:50.973 --> 00:24:53.058
you know, "What the hell
am I living around here for?

475
00:24:53.142 --> 00:24:55.226
"I got no reason to go on."

476
00:24:56.645 --> 00:25:01.107
But with you, kid, boy,
I got a reason to go on,

477
00:25:01.901 --> 00:25:05.904
and I'm gonna stay alive, and
I will watch you make good.

478
00:25:06.322 --> 00:25:07.405
"And I'll never leave you."

479
00:25:07.490 --> 00:25:08.782
And I'll never leave you

480
00:25:08.866 --> 00:25:10.325
until that happens.

481
00:25:10.826 --> 00:25:14.996
'Cause when I leave you, you'll
not only know how to fight,

482
00:25:15.831 --> 00:25:19.084
you'll be able to take care of
yourself outside the ring, too.

483
00:25:19.168 --> 00:25:20.251
Is that okay?

484
00:25:20.336 --> 00:25:21.336
It's okay.

485
00:25:22.171 --> 00:25:23.880
Okay.

486
00:25:23.964 --> 00:25:25.465
Now, I got
a little gift for you.

487
00:25:25.549 --> 00:25:27.425
Mick, you... Now, wait a
minute. Wait a minute now.

488
00:25:27.510 --> 00:25:28.468
Wait a minute.

489
00:25:28.552 --> 00:25:29.719
Really, I don't
need nothing.

490
00:25:29.804 --> 00:25:32.347
Look at this. See that?

491
00:25:32.515 --> 00:25:35.141
This is the favorite thing
that I have on this Earth,

492
00:25:36.435 --> 00:25:38.937
and Rocky Marciano
give me that.

493
00:25:39.730 --> 00:25:41.815
You know what it was?
His cufflink.

494
00:25:43.526 --> 00:25:45.652
And now I'm
giving it to you.

495
00:25:46.904 --> 00:25:49.405
And it is gonna be
like a...

496
00:25:50.366 --> 00:25:53.034
Like an angel on
your shoulder, see?

497
00:25:53.828 --> 00:25:58.540
If you ever get hurt, and you
feel that you're going down,

498
00:25:59.458 --> 00:26:02.585
this little angel is
gonna whisper in your ear.

499
00:26:02.670 --> 00:26:06.506
He's gonna say, "Get up, you son of a bitch,

500
00:26:07.925 --> 00:26:09.509
"'cause Mickey loves you."

501
00:26:10.219 --> 00:26:11.302
Okay?

502
00:26:12.972 --> 00:26:14.264
Thanks, Mick.
All right.

503
00:26:14.348 --> 00:26:16.432
I love you, too.

504
00:26:17.351 --> 00:26:18.726
Go after 'em, kid.

505
00:26:19.895 --> 00:26:21.521
Go after 'em.
Thanks.

506
00:26:26.360 --> 00:26:27.902
You was the angel.

507
00:26:28.988 --> 00:26:30.238
There it is.

508
00:26:30.698 --> 00:26:32.157
What happened to
his other cufflink?

509
00:26:32.241 --> 00:26:34.325
I don't know.
He only give me one.

510
00:26:35.244 --> 00:26:37.078
He gave it to some bum.

511
00:27:27.755 --> 00:27:29.214
Don't worry about these.

512
00:27:29.298 --> 00:27:30.965
All right.
Let's go, Paulie.

513
00:27:31.926 --> 00:27:33.801
I really can't believe it.
This kid's taking this too good.

514
00:27:33.928 --> 00:27:35.553
Need a hand, champ?
No, I got it.

515
00:27:35.638 --> 00:27:38.181
Hey, Rock. It's good I
kept the place, right?

516
00:27:38.265 --> 00:27:39.724
How you doing?
It saves money.

517
00:27:39.808 --> 00:27:41.559
Yeah.
Hey, get back.

518
00:27:41.644 --> 00:27:42.644
Right?

519
00:27:43.145 --> 00:27:46.731
A little aluminum on the
front, hey, it's a winner.

520
00:27:50.277 --> 00:27:51.361
Thank you.

521
00:27:52.905 --> 00:27:55.823
Welcome back, Rocky!
We missed ya!

522
00:27:57.368 --> 00:27:59.661
It's only... It's only temporary, you know?

523
00:28:00.412 --> 00:28:01.955
Come on inside.

524
00:28:04.333 --> 00:28:05.333
Thanks.

525
00:28:13.008 --> 00:28:14.801
- Hello?
- Mrs. Balboa?

526
00:28:14.885 --> 00:28:16.594
George Washington Duke here.

527
00:28:16.679 --> 00:28:17.762
Yes?

528
00:28:17.846 --> 00:28:19.639
Mrs. Balboa, can you hear it?

529
00:28:19.723 --> 00:28:21.933
Listen close,
you must be able to hear it.

530
00:28:23.143 --> 00:28:24.143
Hear what?

531
00:28:24.228 --> 00:28:25.770
The sound of
the parade going by,

532
00:28:25.854 --> 00:28:27.981
of opportunity knocking.

533
00:28:28.065 --> 00:28:30.149
I mean, what's it gonna take
to get you people to realize

534
00:28:30.234 --> 00:28:33.611
I'm giving you a chance to
pull yourselves together again?

535
00:28:33.696 --> 00:28:36.030
Let me handle your husband's
career and the money will pour in.

536
00:28:36.115 --> 00:28:38.574
You can start living
like human beings again.

537
00:28:39.326 --> 00:28:41.577
Listen, Mr. Duke, we're
living like human beings.

538
00:28:41.662 --> 00:28:43.288
You ought to
try it sometime.

539
00:28:44.832 --> 00:28:46.624
You leave my husband alone.

540
00:28:50.337 --> 00:28:51.504
Women.

541
00:28:58.721 --> 00:29:00.430
When'd you
start that?

542
00:29:01.056 --> 00:29:03.433
I don't know. It's like a
bad habit that comes back.

543
00:29:03.517 --> 00:29:04.934
But, hey, listen.

544
00:29:05.019 --> 00:29:08.146
We ain't talking about me,
we're talking about you, right?

545
00:29:08.230 --> 00:29:09.272
Hey, Rocky,
how you doing, man?

546
00:29:09.356 --> 00:29:10.315
Yo. How you doing?

547
00:29:10.399 --> 00:29:11.733
Good to see you back
in the neighborhood.

548
00:29:11.817 --> 00:29:13.109
Yeah. Thank you.
It's great to be back.

549
00:29:13.193 --> 00:29:14.777
You know, you're
real smart in school,

550
00:29:14.862 --> 00:29:17.030
but you gotta be smart
on the street, too, see?

551
00:29:17.114 --> 00:29:18.323
How do you mean?

552
00:29:18.407 --> 00:29:20.116
Well, you gotta know
who the players are

553
00:29:20.200 --> 00:29:22.035
and, like, who you're talking to around here.

554
00:29:22.119 --> 00:29:24.495
Watch out for the scammers.
Everybody's gonna try to scam.

555
00:29:24.580 --> 00:29:26.497
What's a scam?
Ask your father.

556
00:29:26.582 --> 00:29:29.042
Well, a scam is
like a hustle.

557
00:29:29.543 --> 00:29:30.501
He don't get it.

558
00:29:30.586 --> 00:29:32.003
Well, you know, like
a hustle's related to...

559
00:29:32.087 --> 00:29:33.212
Rocky?
Yeah?

560
00:29:33.297 --> 00:29:35.006
Rocky, remember me?
I'm Bubba's mother.

561
00:29:35.090 --> 00:29:36.090
Yeah.

562
00:29:36.175 --> 00:29:37.842
You used to use his head for a punching bag.

563
00:29:37.926 --> 00:29:38.926
Yeah, he had
a nice head.

564
00:29:39.011 --> 00:29:40.178
Welcome back.

565
00:29:41.096 --> 00:29:43.723
So, anyway, like a hustle's
related to a con, you know?

566
00:29:43.807 --> 00:29:45.808
- He don't get it.
- A deception.

567
00:29:45.934 --> 00:29:46.934
Excuse me?

568
00:29:47.019 --> 00:29:48.102
You're saying
beware of deceptions.

569
00:29:48.187 --> 00:29:50.229
Yeah, that's good.
Absolutely.

570
00:29:50.314 --> 00:29:51.647
You're very smart,
you know?

571
00:29:52.816 --> 00:29:56.402
Hey, ain't this where the
Atomic Hoagie shop used to be?

572
00:29:56.487 --> 00:29:58.321
I'm new here,
Dad.

573
00:29:58.614 --> 00:30:00.907
This neighborhood's coming
down with tooth decay.

574
00:30:00.991 --> 00:30:02.408
It's called
urban blight.

575
00:30:02.493 --> 00:30:03.534
Yeah?

576
00:30:04.119 --> 00:30:07.288
I'll tell you something, this
place is blight new, you know?

577
00:30:07.706 --> 00:30:09.665
I think a little aluminum
siding and some paint,

578
00:30:09.750 --> 00:30:11.918
this place could be okay
again. What do you think?

579
00:30:12.002 --> 00:30:13.878
I don't know. Anyway, we're
gonna be late for school. Come on.

580
00:30:13.962 --> 00:30:16.881
Hey, Paulie, I wanna talk to
the kid private, like, you know,

581
00:30:16.965 --> 00:30:18.007
man to smaller man,
all right?

582
00:30:18.092 --> 00:30:19.300
Right.
Like I got no feelings.

583
00:30:19.385 --> 00:30:20.385
Come on, Paulie.

584
00:30:20.469 --> 00:30:21.594
That's how wars start.

585
00:30:21.678 --> 00:30:23.179
Relax, would you?

586
00:30:23.263 --> 00:30:25.181
So, anyway, you know, everybody's
got an angle, you know?

587
00:30:25.265 --> 00:30:27.225
Yo, tough break, Rock.
Yeah.

588
00:30:27.309 --> 00:30:29.060
Everybody's got
a hustle, you know?

589
00:30:29.144 --> 00:30:30.269
See, like these kids around here,

590
00:30:30.354 --> 00:30:31.938
they got street brains,
you see?

591
00:30:32.022 --> 00:30:33.064
That's how they live.

592
00:30:33.148 --> 00:30:34.607
These kids ain't like...
Listen to me.

593
00:30:34.691 --> 00:30:37.652
They ain't like no personalities
that you growed up with.

594
00:30:37.736 --> 00:30:40.363
So you gotta stay very,
very sharp around here.

595
00:30:40.447 --> 00:30:42.031
I intend to.

596
00:30:42.116 --> 00:30:45.660
"Intend." You know, sometimes
you make me feel very stupid.

597
00:30:46.370 --> 00:30:47.912
Why?
Why?

598
00:30:47.996 --> 00:30:49.914
'Cause you're smarter
than me, and that's a fact.

599
00:30:49.998 --> 00:30:51.582
No, I'm not.
Yeah, you are.

600
00:30:51.667 --> 00:30:53.751
It's like every day
you learn something new,

601
00:30:53.836 --> 00:30:55.753
and every day I
forget something new,

602
00:30:55.838 --> 00:30:57.588
but listen.
Listen to me.

603
00:30:57.673 --> 00:31:00.299
We're in this thing together,
so if you can figure out any way

604
00:31:00.384 --> 00:31:02.760
on how to fix things up,
don't be afraid to tell me,

605
00:31:02.845 --> 00:31:05.805
'cause we gotta stick
together, 'cause what are we?

606
00:31:05.889 --> 00:31:07.598
What?

607
00:31:07.683 --> 00:31:08.850
What are we?

608
00:31:09.601 --> 00:31:10.852
Oh, oh...
Home team.

609
00:31:10.936 --> 00:31:12.687
Home team! You know, you got that right.

610
00:31:12.771 --> 00:31:14.439
You know, I used to go to
this school when I was a kid.

611
00:31:14.523 --> 00:31:15.523
You know. Nice bricks.

612
00:31:15.607 --> 00:31:17.608
Used to have good milk
at lunch and everything.

613
00:31:17.693 --> 00:31:18.776
It was real tough then,

614
00:31:18.861 --> 00:31:21.487
but I think you can
handle it, don't you think?

615
00:31:21.572 --> 00:31:24.657
No way, you don't even
know what you're talking about.

616
00:31:24.741 --> 00:31:26.659
If you went here,
I can go here.

617
00:31:27.744 --> 00:31:30.079
I'm not scared, really.

618
00:31:30.164 --> 00:31:31.289
Really?

619
00:31:32.374 --> 00:31:34.792
Well, I guess
I'm a little scared.

620
00:31:34.877 --> 00:31:36.252
But that's normal,
don't you think?

621
00:31:36.336 --> 00:31:38.463
Yeah. You know,
I had 72 fights coming up,

622
00:31:38.547 --> 00:31:40.131
and every one of 'em
I was scared.

623
00:31:40.215 --> 00:31:43.634
So, yeah, you know,
that's real, real normal.

624
00:31:46.638 --> 00:31:47.638
I'll see ya later.

625
00:31:47.723 --> 00:31:48.806
Okay, kid.

626
00:31:48.891 --> 00:31:50.308
Here's the front door.

627
00:31:51.810 --> 00:31:53.728
Okay. Hey, wait!
What's this?

628
00:31:53.812 --> 00:31:54.812
What's...

629
00:31:56.064 --> 00:31:57.106
Goodness gracious.

630
00:31:57.191 --> 00:31:58.649
Where'd this come from?

631
00:31:58.734 --> 00:32:01.861
It's a strange place to stash
your lunch money, don't you think?

632
00:32:01.945 --> 00:32:04.155
It's just a lunch joke, you know?

633
00:32:04.239 --> 00:32:05.281
Thanks, Dad.

634
00:32:05.365 --> 00:32:07.283
Okay, listen.
I'll see you later.

635
00:32:08.076 --> 00:32:10.453
Remember, Daddy loves you.
You're number one.

636
00:32:10.537 --> 00:32:11.662
Home team!

637
00:32:11.747 --> 00:32:14.165
Just be nice, right?
You'll be okay.

638
00:32:15.167 --> 00:32:17.835
And don't mess with
nobody's girlfriend.

639
00:32:17.920 --> 00:32:19.462
They don't like
that around here.

640
00:32:26.386 --> 00:32:28.513
You know, Paulie, I'm
really worried about the kid.

641
00:32:28.597 --> 00:32:30.348
You know, he ain't
used to living like this.

642
00:32:30.432 --> 00:32:32.183
He don't know
the streets or nothing.

643
00:32:32.267 --> 00:32:34.852
And that school, I know
exactly what's gonna happen.

644
00:32:34.937 --> 00:32:37.897
Some wise guy's gonna come
up to him 'cause he's my kid.

645
00:32:37.981 --> 00:32:40.024
He's just gonna come out
and try to bang him out,

646
00:32:40.108 --> 00:32:43.027
give him a cheap shot,
you know? I mean... Jeez.

647
00:32:43.111 --> 00:32:44.195
Mr. Balboa?
Yeah?

648
00:32:44.279 --> 00:32:45.404
How you doing?
My name's Tommy Gunn.

649
00:32:45.489 --> 00:32:46.572
Yeah, how
you doing?

650
00:32:46.657 --> 00:32:48.491
Well, with a name like that,
you better be tough.

651
00:32:48.575 --> 00:32:50.201
Yeah, very true.
It ain't easy.

652
00:32:50.285 --> 00:32:51.661
Anyway, I come
from Oklahoma.

653
00:32:51.745 --> 00:32:52.745
Welcome.

654
00:32:52.829 --> 00:32:54.038
I have an amateur's
record of 45-to-one.

655
00:32:54.122 --> 00:32:56.123
And I turned pro at 18,
and I had eight fights.

656
00:32:56.208 --> 00:32:58.000
You're a fighter?
Yeah, I'm a fighter.

657
00:32:58.085 --> 00:33:00.962
And now that I'm 20, I'd just
like to show you what I got.

658
00:33:01.088 --> 00:33:02.880
Well, I... I mean, I've
saved up about 400 bucks.

659
00:33:02.965 --> 00:33:04.382
Mr. Rocky Balboa. I could
pay you for training.

660
00:33:04.466 --> 00:33:05.508
Yeah... What?

661
00:33:05.592 --> 00:33:07.301
Excuse me, young man,
I have some business here.

662
00:33:07.386 --> 00:33:08.553
What, is he lost or what?
Thank you.

663
00:33:08.637 --> 00:33:09.845
Good to see you again, friend. How you doing?

664
00:33:09.930 --> 00:33:10.888
Yeah. How you doing?

665
00:33:10.973 --> 00:33:12.557
My health is fine.
What more could a man ask for?

666
00:33:12.641 --> 00:33:13.599
Money and hair.

667
00:33:13.684 --> 00:33:14.892
Listen, I gotta
go to work now.

668
00:33:14.977 --> 00:33:16.060
What? Where? Here? In a sweatbox?

669
00:33:16.144 --> 00:33:17.144
Yeah.

670
00:33:17.229 --> 00:33:18.354
Can't be good
for the image.

671
00:33:18.438 --> 00:33:19.855
Urban light.
What are you gonna do?

672
00:33:19.940 --> 00:33:21.399
Hey, Rocky, Rocky...
What'd you say?

673
00:33:21.483 --> 00:33:23.484
Urban light. It's "blight." Urban blight.

674
00:33:23.610 --> 00:33:24.735
Rock, George would
like you to consider

675
00:33:24.820 --> 00:33:26.153
putting on those
damn gloves again.

676
00:33:26.238 --> 00:33:27.905
It's a hell of
a payday.

677
00:33:27.990 --> 00:33:29.407
Well, you know,
I'm officially expired.

678
00:33:29.491 --> 00:33:30.866
No, you do have
marquee value.

679
00:33:30.951 --> 00:33:32.743
You put butts in the
buckets, asses in the seats.

680
00:33:32.828 --> 00:33:34.412
A businessman with
any sort of brain

681
00:33:34.496 --> 00:33:36.747
don't retire when he can
still pull in the bread, baby.

682
00:33:36.832 --> 00:33:38.958
'Cause only in America do we
get these kind of opportunities.

683
00:33:39.042 --> 00:33:41.377
Union Cane's going for the title on the 14th.

684
00:33:41.461 --> 00:33:43.087
Yeah, here's some tickets. Be our guests.

685
00:33:43.171 --> 00:33:44.297
We have a strong
feeling about this one.

686
00:33:44.381 --> 00:33:45.506
Think he's gonna take it.

687
00:33:45.591 --> 00:33:46.757
That's the time
to challenge.

688
00:33:46.842 --> 00:33:48.884
Because people
love comebacks,

689
00:33:48.969 --> 00:33:51.262
and there's nothing in the
boxing business more commercial

690
00:33:51.346 --> 00:33:52.597
than a long-shot comeback

691
00:33:52.681 --> 00:33:55.057
of a down-on-his-luck,
pure snow-white underdog.

692
00:33:55.142 --> 00:33:56.767
Now, like your
Mark Twain once said,

693
00:33:56.852 --> 00:33:59.312
"Virtue has never been
as respectable as money."

694
00:33:59.396 --> 00:34:00.855
Who's Twain?
He was a painter.

695
00:34:00.939 --> 00:34:03.566
Look, simply put,
you're the great white hope.

696
00:34:03.650 --> 00:34:04.692
You mean great white dope.
No, forget it.

697
00:34:04.776 --> 00:34:05.776
No, no,
Rock, Rock...

698
00:34:05.861 --> 00:34:06.944
I ain't emotionally
involved in boxing...

699
00:34:07.029 --> 00:34:08.863
Hey, hold it.
Hold the bullshit.

700
00:34:08.947 --> 00:34:10.948
I know what the problem is.
You think I was born yesterday?

701
00:34:11.033 --> 00:34:12.325
Merlin, show him
the paper.

702
00:34:12.409 --> 00:34:14.118
What paper? Now, this is your medical report.

703
00:34:14.202 --> 00:34:16.245
It's not so good, but we can work around it.

704
00:34:16.330 --> 00:34:17.288
Where'd you get this?

705
00:34:17.372 --> 00:34:18.623
It really doesn't matter,
does it, Rock?

706
00:34:18.707 --> 00:34:20.625
You agree to fight Cane,
and George here can guarantee

707
00:34:20.709 --> 00:34:22.168
you get licensed in any
country around the world.

708
00:34:22.252 --> 00:34:23.878
Guaranteed.
You can do this?

709
00:34:23.962 --> 00:34:24.962
No problem.

710
00:34:25.047 --> 00:34:26.922
His comeback's in the bag
and worth millions.

711
00:34:27.007 --> 00:34:29.383
The time is hot, the deal is hot. Caliente!

712
00:34:29.468 --> 00:34:31.260
We could use one more payday. I agree!

713
00:34:31.345 --> 00:34:32.595
Adrian, where'd
you come from?

714
00:34:32.679 --> 00:34:33.846
What do you
think you're going?

715
00:34:33.930 --> 00:34:36.098
Mrs. Balboa just appeared.
This woman is magic.

716
00:34:36.183 --> 00:34:37.642
Look, I don't think
you're very funny.

717
00:34:37.726 --> 00:34:39.602
Are you trying to talk my
husband into fighting again?

718
00:34:39.686 --> 00:34:41.228
We're talking business,
now, darling.

719
00:34:41.313 --> 00:34:43.230
Do you like feeling hard up?

720
00:34:43.315 --> 00:34:45.941
Do you like reaching in your
pocket and only feeling your leg?

721
00:34:46.026 --> 00:34:47.985
Well, do you?
I didn't think so.

722
00:34:48.070 --> 00:34:50.196
I'm offering you your last golden opportunity

723
00:34:50.280 --> 00:34:51.572
to dump this loser image.

724
00:34:51.657 --> 00:34:52.865
Who you talking to?

725
00:34:52.949 --> 00:34:54.241
Hey, Adrian, you weren't working across...

726
00:34:54.326 --> 00:34:57.453
Hey, what the hell are you
two people talking about?

727
00:34:57.537 --> 00:34:59.038
This is
a tremendous opportunity.

728
00:34:59.122 --> 00:35:00.581
Opportunity for who?

729
00:35:00.666 --> 00:35:03.209
For you to make money?
For him to be disabled?

730
00:35:03.293 --> 00:35:05.711
What would you do if the
choices were reversed?

731
00:35:06.129 --> 00:35:07.922
You have to
think about that.

732
00:35:08.590 --> 00:35:10.925
Rocky, they don't
care about you.

733
00:35:11.843 --> 00:35:14.011
You want to get serious?
Let's get serious.

734
00:35:14.096 --> 00:35:16.681
You represent the dreams of the
long shots, the little people.

735
00:35:16.765 --> 00:35:18.307
The never-wills
identify with you,

736
00:35:18.392 --> 00:35:20.351
and identification is
the key to public success.

737
00:35:20.435 --> 00:35:23.354
You're a true champion, a true
product of the people. Now sell it.

738
00:35:23.438 --> 00:35:25.231
Sell it while
there are still buyers.

739
00:35:25.315 --> 00:35:26.315
They ain't
gonna last forever.

740
00:35:26.400 --> 00:35:27.483
You say you're a fighter?
Then fight!

741
00:35:27.567 --> 00:35:29.485
You say you want a champion's do, then do it

742
00:35:29.569 --> 00:35:32.196
and I'll make you so much
money you could swim in it!

743
00:35:32.280 --> 00:35:33.906
You can swim,
can't you, darling?

744
00:35:33.990 --> 00:35:35.574
What do you say?
